The paper discusses optimization methods for machine learning, specifically for minimizing strongly-convex functions under an interpolation condition satisfied by over-parameterized models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper discusses stochastic second order methods, which are numerical optimization techniques, indicating that it could also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) category. The paper also evaluates the methods on synthetic and real datasets, suggesting that it could belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computer vision (cs.CV), or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories.
